parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or near-misses, especially when riding in heavy traffic or navigating intersections.
symptoms: when taking off from a stop
or when accelerating from a low RPM. The motorcycle may hesitate or stutter before stalling
and the stalling can occur frequently

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected stalling of the engine can cause the motorcycle to lose power, leading to accidents, falls, and injuries, especially when happening in traffic or during turns.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies suddenly
often when accelerating from a stop
and may occur repeatedly; the motorcycle may fall or become difficult to control
putting the rider at risk of injury or accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of power and control, leading to accidents, especially at high speeds, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the engine stutters or hesitates before stalling.
